==English==

===Etymology===
Old English ''[[sped#Old English|spēd]]'', from Germanic ''*spodiz''.  Cognate with Dutch ''[[spoed]]''.

===Pronunciation===
*{{IPA|/spiːd/}}
*Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-iːd|-iːd]]

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# {{archaic}} Luck, success, prosperity.
# The fact or quality of moving quickly; [[rapidity]]; rapid action or motion
# The rate of motion or action, specifically {{math}}/{{physics}} the magnitude of the [[velocity]]; the rate [[distance]] is traversed in a given [[time]].
# {{photography}} The sensitivity to light of [[film]], [[plates]], etc.; [[shutter speed]]
# {{slang}} Any illegal amphetamine drug, especially [[methamphetamine]].

